law.text:
As used in KRS 154.47-105 to 154.47-120, unless the context clearly indicates otherwise:
"Certified tree farmer" means a person whose tree farm is certified by the Kentucky Tree Farm Committee and approved by the Kentucky Department for Natural Resources, Division of Forestry;
"Council" means the Kentucky Forest Products Council;
"Forest steward" means a person whose forest property is certified as a stewardship forest and approved by the Kentucky Department for Natural Resources, Division of Forestry; and
"Procurement area" means an area specified by the applicant in radius of miles from the applicant's site of operations from which the applicant acquires raw wood products.
